===============================================
==  CP-PAW distribution                      ==
===============================================

Installation:
-------------
1) decide on an architecture name ARCH such as "g95_blechtrottel".
   It is recommended to use the convention ARCH=compilername_computername
   where you replaced compilername and computer name according to your system
1) make a copy of the example parameter file "parms.example" named "parms.ARCH", 
2) edit the new parameter file "parms.${ARCH}" following the instructions given therein
3) execute "./configure --with-parmfile=parms.${ARCH}"
4) execute "make docs" 
4) execute "make small" 

The CP-PAW executable will be
   bin/${ARCH}/paw_fast.x
   bin/${ARCH}/paw_fast_parallel.x

The documentation will be
   doc/manual.pdf
   doc/history.pdf
   doc/manual.pdf  (corrently not yet useful)

Prerequisites:
--------------
Your directory should look like this

configure            configure file
configure.ac         (not needed: input file for creating configure with autoconf)
dx                   data explorer programs
Makefile_bare.in     used by configure to create makefiles
Makefile_targets.in  used by configure to create makefiles
parameters           parameter directory
parms.example        example parameter file
parms.g95
src                  source directory

